Date of Birth: October 24, 1883<br/>
Birthplace: Granger, Utah, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: April 10, 1958<br/>
Death: December 2, 1975<br/>
<br/>
Born Oct. 24, 1883, at Granger, Salt Lake Co., Utah, to Homer Manly Brown and Lydia Jane Brown. Sustained as Assistant to the Twelve Oct. 4, 1953, at age 69; ordained an apostle April 10, 1958, by David 0. McKay, at age 74; sustained as counselor in the First Presidency June 22,1961; sustained as second counselor to President McKay Oct. 12,1961; sustained as first counselor to President McKay Oct. 4,1963; released at death of President McKay Jan. 18, 1970, and resumed position in the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles; died Dec. 2, 1975, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 92.